Key Match Events: Thabang Sesinyi scored the only goal of the match in the 52nd minute for Botswana.
Omaatla Kebatho and Kabelo Seakanyeng of Botswana received yellow cards in the 80th and 79th minutes respectively.
Gift Moyo of Botswana was substituted in the 90th minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Francistown Stadium in Francistown, Botswana, with an attendance of 8,000.
The referee for the match was Messie Jessie Nkounkou Mvoutou.
Others: The final score was Botswana 1, Cape Verde Islands 0.
Botswana's win moves them to 2-0-2 in the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations Qualifying, Group Stage with 6 points, while Cape Verde Islands are 1-0-3 with 3 points.
